answers.body_markdown:
This:

    synchronized( someGetMethod() ) {
    // synchronized block
    }

is the same as

    Object obj = someGetMethod();
    synchronized( obj ) {
    // synchronized block
    }

So no, `someGetMethod()` is not invoked in a synchronized way.

If you want it to be synchronized, you either have to declare the method synchronized, or explicitly synchronize, for example:

    synchronized (this) {
      synchronized( someGetMethod() ) {
        // synchronized block
      }
    }

